result.formatted_address: The Arcade, 100 Cyberport Rd, Telegraph Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: El Charro Mexican Cantina

reviews.text: Food was less than satisfactory. Service was good, very kind and friendly staff. Good place for kids. Festive decor. But definitely not good Mexican food- left hungry and disappointed. Kids liked their chicken fingers and fries though.

Family friendly,  lots of things to keep children entertained.  Nice decoration and Mexican hats.  Menu has quite a lot of choice. Tried the nachos although found them to be pretty standard.  Suggest to go for something like sizzling fajitas or the soup instead.

I went there around 2-3pm Saturday... somehow it’s empty which surprised me but Cyberport is always empty except the movie theater 
The food was great and good to me. May be it’s not the same as elsewhere but I am super satisfied. Food quality is above average, price is ok.... service cannot comment as it’s empty.... nice chill out and have a glass of wine or beer or drinks...
Good place to go with kids, with small baby zone. Food quality is OK but choice is a bit limited
The food was Tex Mex fare similar to some other places in Hong Kong but better quality. The guacamole was fresh tasting. I would definitely recommend this restaurant.
